sql:
SELECT experiment_id
FROM experiment_results
WHERE yield_per_acre = (
    SELECT MAX(yield_per_acre)
    FROM experiment_results
);

SELECT measurement_date, plant_stand
FROM plant_measurements
ORDER BY measurement_date ASC;

SELECT COUNT(application_record_id) AS number_of_records
FROM boron_applications
WHERE experiment_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
- Boron application is a common agricultural practice to promote plant growth and yield; 
- Average plant stand is an indicator of plant health and growth; 
- Different application methods and schedules may have varying effects on plant growth; 
- This analysis can help farmers or researchers optimize their boron application strategies for better crop yields.
